Class ContextualNavigationCommand

java.lang.Object
gw.api.quickjump.QuickjumpCommand
gw.api.quickjump.StaticNavigationCommand
gw.api.quickjump.ContextualNavigationCommand
All Implemented Interfaces:
ChainableQuickjumpCommand
Direct Known Subclasses:
ClaimContextualNewDocumentTemplateCommand, ClaimContextualNewEmailCommand, ClaimContextualNewNoteCommand, ClaimContextualNewRecoveryReserveCommand
public class ContextualNavigationCommand extends StaticNavigationCommand
QuickJump command which takes the user to a particular location, using a parameter found on the current location.

    • getKey

      public String getKey()
      Returns a String used to uniquely identify this command, for the purpose of detecting duplicate command definitions. Subclasses should only override this method if two instances of the subclass should be permitted to share a command name - this will only be the case if said instances can be guaranteed never to be available to the user at the same time.
